                  <persName corresp="PRS0000" instant="false" full="yes">The original owner of the Ms. was probably Gäbrä Ṣǝyon mentioned in the concluding supplication formulas on fols. 59vb and 63ra (s. also fols. 3va, 4ra, 66rb) and in the prayers of Text V. On fols. 15vb, 31ra, 59vb and 63ra, other individuals are mentioned: Qäṣäla Giyorgis, Gäbrä ʾIyäsus, Gäbrä Śǝllase, Wälättä Kidan and “the children of the community” (däqiqä maḫbär).  &#xD;
Later, the Ms. was bought by Gäbrä Mädḫǝn who donated it to [the tabot of] the Saviour of the World of the church ʾIyäsus (s. Additio 1). His name and the name of his wife are crudely added interlineally on fols. 31ra, 55va.</persName>
